!item [Syntax:]
int32_t read_config_byte (int32_t handle, uint8_t reg, uint8_t *adresse);

!item [Description:]
This function read data from the PCI configuration space of a given
card.

!begin_xlist [Parameters]
!item [handle]
Device handle

!item [reg]
Register number (0,1,2,... for Byte access)

!item [adresse]
Pointer to space for read data

!end_xlist

!item [(!nolink [Return]) Value:]
